25/02/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Leaders of the ruling National Liberal Party (PNL) and the Social Democratic Party (PSD) proposed on Sunday (February 24th) holding general and local elections on the same day later this year. 
As of now, local elections are held in May and general elections in November. 
The PSD proposes both votes take place on June 28th, while the PNL has suggested no particular date. 
(Rompres, Nine O'clock- 25/02/08; Mediafax - 24/02/08)
